#: includes/abilities/add-tpgb-hovercard.php:18
msgid "Add Nexter Blocks Hover Card"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/add-tpgb-hovercard.php:19
msgid ""
"Adds the Nexter Blocks Hover Card block (tpgb/tp-hovercard) — a flexible HTML structure builder that creates hoverable card layouts by composing nested HTML tags (div, a, span, p, h1-h6) with content types (text, image, custom HTML, or container-only). Each card is built from a list of \"items\" where each item is either an open tag, close tag, or content element. Supports per-element positioning, typography, shadows, backgrounds, borders, and link wrappers. This is a dynamic block.\n"
"\n"
"USAGE: Pass a \"cards\" array of item objects. Each item represents one HTML element:\n"
"  - { openTag: \"div\", content: \"none\" } → starts a div container\n"
"  - { openTag: \"a\", aLink: {url: \"...\"}, content: \"none\" } → starts an anchor\n"
"  - { openTag: \"h3\", content: \"text\", cntText: \"Title\" } → opens h3 with text\n"
"  - { content: \"text\", cntText: \"Some text\" } → standalone text\n"
"  - { content: \"img\", imageUrl: \"...\" } → an image element\n"
"  - { closeTag: \"close\" } → closes the most recent open tag\n"
"\n"
"IMPORTANT: Every openTag must have a matching closeTag in the correct order (nested properly)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/add-tpgb-hovercard.php:623
msgid "tpgb/tp-hovercard is not registered."
msgstr ""

